name: Canadian Walleye (Pickerel)
author: kathleen
summary: You can cook this classic Canadian shore lunch indoors all year round when you don't have the time or the luxury of getting out on the lake! Serve with lots of lemon wedges or vinegar.
directions: Heat  1/8 inch of vegetable oil in two large cast-iron or heavy-duty frying pans over medium-high heat
Arrange three separate pie plates or shallow bowls for breading the fish
Combine flour, salt and pepper in one bowl, milk and eggs in another, and bread crumbs in the third bowl
Coat each fillet in the flour mixture, then dredge them in egg wash, then coat them well with bread crumbs
Place 4 fillets in each frying pan
Cook until golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes per side
Drain on paper towels and serve immediately
